description: The NASA IceBridge Riegl Laser Altimeter L0 Raw Ranges (ILUTP0) data set contains range to surface measurements taken over Antarctica using the Riegl LD90-3800-HiP-LR Distance Meter. The data were collected by scientists working on the Investigating the Cryospheric Evolution of the Central Antarctic Plate (ICECAP) project, which is funded by the National Science Foundation (NSF) and the Natural Environment Research Council (NERC) with additional support from NASA Operation IceBridge. The data are stored in ASCII text format and are available for periodic, ongoing campaigns from 2009 to the present via FTP.
name: IceBridge Riegl Laser Altimeter L0 Raw Ranges
